WEBVTT

00:18.770 --> 00:22.607
MORBO: Welcome to Entertainment
and Earth Invasion Tonite!

00:28.821 --> 00:31.115
We'll be talking
with General Extermulo,

00:31.241 --> 00:33.451
who will crush the human
race under his boot

00:33.535 --> 00:35.954
unless his demands
are met immediately!

00:36.037 --> 00:38.623
But first, celebrity buzz.
Linda?

00:38.790 --> 00:39.999
(LAUGHS)

00:40.124 --> 00:43.169
it has now been one year
since the death of Calculon,

00:43.253 --> 00:46.506
<i>former star of TV soap opera
All</i> My <i>Circuits.</i>

00:46.798 --> 00:49.801
<i>The celebrated robot
actor killed himself onstage</i>

00:49.884 --> 00:52.512
<i>in a failed attempt to make a
death scene more convincing.</i>

00:53.721 --> 00:56.933
Here at his gravesite, loyal fans
have turned out by the several

00:57.016 --> 00:59.727
to pay tribute to
the legendary ham.

00:59.811 --> 01:01.437
What brings you
two here today?

01:01.521 --> 01:03.731
We came to honor
Calculon's memory.

01:03.815 --> 01:06.401
<i>Ever since he died,
All My Circuits is terrible.</i>

01:06.484 --> 01:08.570
It's not even
worth watching anymore.

01:09.153 --> 01:11.447
(GASPS) Fry! All <i>My</i> Circuits
is on in three minutes!

01:11.531 --> 01:13.366
What? We got to get home!

01:14.826 --> 01:15.910
(BENDER CHUCKLES)

01:16.035 --> 01:17.161
Hey!

01:19.956 --> 01:22.000
BOTH: <i>All My Circuits!
All My Circuits!</i>

01:22.125 --> 01:23.334
(BOTH EXCLAIMING)

01:23.835 --> 01:26.671
ANNOUNCER: And now All My
Circuits, brought to you <i>by</i>

01:26.754 --> 01:30.842
<i>Anonyco, the unknown company
doing unknown things.</i>

01:31.426 --> 01:32.677
<i>Oh, Vaxtron,</i>

01:32.760 --> 01:34.804
it's been a year
since my ugly husband

01:34.929 --> 01:36.973
Calculon disappeared
without a trace,

01:37.056 --> 01:40.518
evidently forced into servitude
aboard a crab fishing boat.

01:40.602 --> 01:43.104
So he's, like,
legally dead now.

01:43.187 --> 01:44.897
Want to get
married and whatever?

01:45.106 --> 01:47.650
Ugh! The new guy is so boring.

01:47.734 --> 01:51.738
I like him. His acting is much
more subtle than Calculon's.

01:51.821 --> 01:54.115
Vaxtron, I have
to tell you something.

01:54.198 --> 01:55.533
I'm pregnant.

01:55.617 --> 01:57.201
And you're not the father!

01:57.327 --> 01:59.287
(DRAMATIC MUSIC)

01:59.871 --> 02:00.872
Okey-doke.

02:00.955 --> 02:03.958
You see? You see? Calculon would
have acted the crap out of that.

02:04.042 --> 02:07.045
He would've acted so hard, the
camera would've broken down.

02:07.128 --> 02:08.211
In tears!

02:08.378 --> 02:09.464
I'm changing the channel.

02:10.214 --> 02:11.507
(PLAYING SOLEMN TUNE)

02:13.676 --> 02:17.055
Man, Bender and I used to love
watching All <i>My</i> Circuits together.

02:17.138 --> 02:19.807
Now what are we supposed to do
at the office instead of work?

02:19.891 --> 02:21.184
How about
talking to each other?

02:21.267 --> 02:23.478
That's what bath time is for.

02:23.561 --> 02:27.065
If we talk to each other any more
than that, it'll ruin our friendship.

02:27.148 --> 02:30.610
Oh! If only we could bring
Calculon back to life somehow.

02:30.693 --> 02:32.654
You can.
What?

02:32.737 --> 02:34.822
It's simple, you simpletons.

02:34.906 --> 02:37.283
Calculon is a robot,
a mere mechanism

02:37.367 --> 02:39.911
that can easily be restored
to working order.

02:39.994 --> 02:43.706
The only problem is we would
need his physical remains.

02:43.790 --> 02:45.625
Hang on a sec.

02:46.084 --> 02:47.168
(SCATTING)

02:48.211 --> 02:50.797
<i>This must be
a difficult time for people</i>

02:50.922 --> 02:53.591
<i>who confuse TV actors
with actual friends.</i>

02:54.634 --> 02:56.803
<i>Dear God! What is he doing?</i>
(MAN <i>SCREAMING)</i>

02:56.886 --> 02:59.889
<i>No! Somebody stop him!</i>

