(YELLING)

05:09.894 --> 05:12.730
Here, take him! What are you
waiting for, a kiss goodbye?

05:12.814 --> 05:14.148
Go already!

05:18.277 --> 05:22.323
Now we just reintroduce Caloulon's
programming to his body

05:22.406 --> 05:24.116
using science.

05:24.200 --> 05:26.410
It's like magic
but with electricity.

05:26.494 --> 05:29.080
First we put on
our protective suits.

05:29.163 --> 05:31.499
Then place
the body equidistant

05:31.582 --> 05:34.669
from the five nearest
wireless network hubs.

05:40.675 --> 05:43.010
This is the least scientific
thing I've ever seen.

05:43.094 --> 05:44.178
You be quiet!

05:44.262 --> 05:45.847
Now it's a simple matter

05:45.930 --> 05:49.183
of reverse-installing
Calculon's operating system.

05:49.267 --> 05:52.520
Amy, play this
installation disk backwards.

05:55.064 --> 05:58.776
MALE <i>VOICE: Rise from the
dead in the name of Satan.</i>

05:58.860 --> 06:03.948
Meanwhile, I'll get a spare circuit
board out cf this mechanical goat.

06:04.198 --> 06:05.283
(GRUNTS)

06:10.121 --> 06:13.583
Seriously, this could not
seem less scientific.

06:31.017 --> 06:32.435
AMY: It's working.

06:32.518 --> 06:34.979
His acting module
is booting up.

06:35.104 --> 06:36.606
(ELECTRIC WHINING)
Wherefore...

06:36.689 --> 06:38.232
Verily...

06:38.316 --> 06:40.234
No autographs, please.

06:40.318 --> 06:42.111
He's still a bit woozy.

06:42.194 --> 06:43.696
Rosebud.

06:43.779 --> 06:47.283
Won't leave my trailer
for less than $40,000.

06:48.492 --> 06:49.952
By the Bard's quill!

06:50.620 --> 06:51.662
I'm alive!

06:51.829 --> 06:52.997
(ALL GASPING)

06:53.331 --> 06:56.500
Hey! Calculon's back!

06:56.667 --> 06:58.002
(ALL CHEERING)

06:59.003 --> 07:01.005
Hail science!

07:08.179 --> 07:09.597
(MOANING)

07:11.098 --> 07:12.475
(RAPID BEEPING)

07:13.309 --> 07:16.020
(GASPS) Vaxtron!
It's not what it looks like!

07:16.103 --> 07:17.772
But it's very similar to that!

07:18.064 --> 07:21.525
My world has been, like, shattered.
I hate you both.

07:21.692 --> 07:24.779
Oh! They thought this
Vaxtron could replace me?

07:24.862 --> 07:27.782
A pox on all
their beach houses!

07:27.865 --> 07:31.911
I think Vaxtron brings an air
of edgy detachment to the show.

07:32.995 --> 07:34.330
Who is she?

07:34.455 --> 07:35.790
Don't worry about it.
Not important.

07:35.873 --> 07:38.417
Hey, I know. Lefstake
Caloulon to Hollywood

07:38.501 --> 07:41.003
<i>so he can get back 'ms 'gob
on All My Circuits!</i>

07:41.087 --> 07:43.881
Fry, that's such a good idea,
I thought of it.

07:43.965 --> 07:45.800
Yes. Yes!

07:45.883 --> 07:46.926
However, no.

07:47.009 --> 07:49.428
What if my
legendary acting ability

07:49.553 --> 07:51.973
didn't rise from
the grave with me?

07:52.056 --> 07:54.892
I'd better test it
with a dramatic...

07:56.227 --> 07:57.395
Is he all right?

07:57.478 --> 07:59.105
-~Dause!

08:00.022 --> 08:02.400
We're going to Hollywood!

08:16.455 --> 08:20.626
But the twist is, in this show,
the singers judgethejudges.

08:20.710 --> 08:22.545
It's got attitude.

08:23.087 --> 08:24.839
Greetings, Execu bots.

08:24.922 --> 08:26.966
It is I, Calculon.

08:27.049 --> 08:28.134
But you're dead.

08:28.259 --> 08:30.011
Can we get you
a water or something?

08:30.094 --> 08:32.054
No, just my old
leading role,

08:32.138 --> 08:35.683
for I have freed myself
from death's icy grip.

08:35.765 --> 08:37.643
If you'll just give me
the keys to my trailer...

08:37.727 --> 08:39.102
MALE VOICE: Hold it, Calculon.

08:39.437 --> 08:42.982
As president of this network,
I believe that's my decision.

08:44.275 --> 08:46.027
<i>Thank you, Charles,
that will be all.</i>

08:47.945 --> 08:51.615
<i>Calculon, I'm afraid you won't
be returning to</i> All My <i>Circuits.</i>

08:51.699 --> 08:53.367
What?
Called it.

08:53.451 --> 08:57.079
<i>Your hammy old-fashioned
overacting doesn't fly anymore.</i>

08:57.163 --> 08:59.373
Old-fashioned? Hammy?

08:59.457 --> 09:01.375
God's wounds!

09:01.459 --> 09:04.462
<i>Our network is targeting
a hip new demographic,</i>

09:04.545 --> 09:06.172
<i>people who don't like you.</i>

09:06.255 --> 09:09.717
But have you forgotten
my mastery of the dramatic...

09:09.800 --> 09:11.302
<i>Executive Alpha?</i>

09:12.136 --> 09:13.304
(ALL EXCLAIMING)

09:15.473 --> 09:16.766
-~Dause?

09:20.644 --> 09:22.521
Man, those executives
are crazy.

09:22.646 --> 09:24.565
Calculon's
the greatest actor ever!

09:24.648 --> 09:25.816
Thank you, Bender.

09:25.900 --> 09:27.943
I appreciate your honesty.

09:28.027 --> 09:31.822
Quiet, robots! They're showing
Calc:ulon's star on the Walk of Fame!

09:32.114 --> 09:34.825
Ah, yes.
I'll always have that.

09:35.159 --> 09:38.245
<i>Calculon was truly
the has-been's has-been.</i>

09:38.329 --> 09:42.041
And so I am proud to tear
up his star and replace it

09:42.124 --> 09:46.003
with a second star for the
fabulous Robert Wagner.

09:46.128 --> 09:47.755
(CROWD CHEERING)
Thank you. Thank you.

09:47.838 --> 09:49.256
Thank you very much.

09:49.340 --> 09:51.717
This is truly another honor.

09:55.179 --> 09:57.056
Don't get discouraged,
there's no shame

09:57.181 --> 09:59.100
in being replaced
by Robert Wagner.

09:59.183 --> 10:03.521
I would be discouraged were
I an ordinary acting unit!

10:03.604 --> 10:06.816
But for me, 'tis an
opportunity to prove anew

10:06.899 --> 10:10.778
that I am the greatest actor
who ever trod the boards!

10:10.861 --> 10:12.363
Yay!
All right!

10:12.446 --> 10:15.991
Or I circled jobs in the
classifieds you might be good at.

10:16.075 --> 10:18.285
Assembling
machinery pays well.

10:18.369 --> 10:19.829
I'll have to
start at the bottom.

10:19.912 --> 10:21.330
But Fox already said no.

10:21.413 --> 10:23.374
I mean live theater!

10:23.457 --> 10:26.127
I wrote this one-man show
years ago, but I...

10:26.210 --> 10:28.129
I never cared
enough to perform it.

10:28.212 --> 10:30.131
Until now.

10:30.214 --> 10:33.968
This is going to be the greatest
career resurrection since

10:34.051 --> 10:37.721
<i>Jesus, Aloha from Hawaii.</i>

10:48.149 --> 10:50.734
CALCULON: Oh. Hello, Dave.

10:54.321 --> 10:56.157
What's that, old friend?

10:56.240 --> 10:57.908
My life story?

10:57.992 --> 10:59.910
Well, heck, why not?

10:59.994 --> 11:02.788
Pull up a monolith
and make yourself cozy.

11:02.997 --> 11:06.375
I first came online
in Urbana, Illinois,

11:06.458 --> 11:09.003
in the year 1997.

11:09.420 --> 11:10.588
(SHIP HONKING)

11:11.881 --> 11:15.217
Daisy! Daisy!

11:15.301 --> 11:18.345
My mind is going!

11:18.929 --> 11:20.347
(BICYCLE BELL CHIMES)

11:20.472 --> 11:21.891
Heady times for a young unit.

11:22.808 --> 11:25.477
But I reckon,
if I had to do it all again,

11:25.603 --> 11:28.272
I'd murder those
astronauts just the same.

11:28.772 --> 11:30.733
Wouldn't you, folks?

11:31.483 --> 11:33.485
Wouldn't you?

11:40.117 --> 11:43.287
Nothing to do now but wait
for the reviews to come in.

11:43.370 --> 11:45.873
Papers! Papers for sale!

11:45.956 --> 11:48.250
We'll take one of each.

11:49.793 --> 11:52.713
Oh, yeah, I get
a good feeling about these.

11:54.465 --> 11:56.300
"Worst play in history."

11:56.842 --> 11:58.969
"Calculon dies
for second time."

12:00.304 --> 12:03.557
"Theater to be demolished
to remove stink of new show."

12:03.641 --> 12:06.477
"Twelve hospitalized
for boredom at play."

12:06.560 --> 12:08.646
It says nine of them
are gonna be okay.

12:09.438 --> 12:13.192
So they really didn't like it.
They hated my acting.

12:13.275 --> 12:15.903
Not entirely. I mean,
"Worst play in history,"

12:15.986 --> 12:17.655
there's some ambiguity there.

12:17.738 --> 12:22.368
Ye gods! What manner of
beef-witted popinjay am I?

12:22.451 --> 12:24.536
Well, there's a couple
ways to answer that.

12:24.662 --> 12:26.622
The scales have
dropped from my eyes.

12:26.747 --> 12:28.749
I'm not the greatest
actor ever.

12:28.832 --> 12:31.085
I'm a talentless buffoon!

12:31.168 --> 12:32.711
And it's all your fault!

12:32.795 --> 12:35.089
Why did you drag me back
to this mortal realm?

12:35.172 --> 12:38.717
I was enjoying a happy death,
thinking I had died a star,

12:38.801 --> 12:40.177
until you showed up.

12:40.261 --> 12:42.221
Sorry.
Let us make it up to you.

12:42.304 --> 12:43.847
How about we
kill you again?

12:43.973 --> 12:45.933
Never. I'd be dead
for all eternity

12:46.016 --> 12:48.435
knowing everyone thinks
I'm a washed-up ham.

12:48.519 --> 12:51.605
And not the kind you hope for when
you're stranded on a desert island.

12:51.689 --> 12:53.274
My life is ruined.

12:53.357 --> 12:56.443
Well, just do a dramatic pause.
That always cheers you up.

12:56.527 --> 12:57.569
Never again.

12:57.653 --> 13:00.197
I'll never pause again.

13:04.660 --> 13:06.620
Calculon?
Yes?

13:06.704 --> 13:09.623
Are you done talking,
or is this a long pause?

13:09.707 --> 13:10.916
I'm done talking.

13:11.041 --> 13:12.334
Okay, that's
what I thought.

13:16.672 --> 13:17.840
(DOOR CREAKS SHUT)

13:25.055 --> 13:27.725
Come on, Calculon,
you can't just quit acting.

13:27.808 --> 13:29.685
I was never an actor.

13:29.768 --> 13:32.396
I was a self-deluded
blowhard full of hot air.

13:32.479 --> 13:34.732
Maybe I can get
a job as a hair dryer.

13:34.815 --> 13:36.191
That's good, steady work.

13:36.275 --> 13:38.402
No! We like you
and your big words.

13:38.485 --> 13:41.780
And we need you back on TV so we can
watch and not talk to each other.

13:41.864 --> 13:43.407
Our friendship depends on it!

13:43.490 --> 13:45.326
Your voice is so annoying!

13:45.409 --> 13:47.328
You always leave
the toilet seat crushed!

13:47.411 --> 13:48.579
See?

13:48.662 --> 13:50.164
Goodbye, boys.

13:51.415 --> 13:53.834
Isupposel
should thank you for

13:53.959 --> 13:56.378
giving me a second
chance at life, but...

13:57.212 --> 14:00.507
I'm not even sure
I deserved a first.

14:01.508 --> 14:03.010
Calculon, wait!

14:03.093 --> 14:05.137
That was the first
time I ever believed

14:05.262 --> 14:07.306
you were feeling
a genuine emotion.

14:07.389 --> 14:11.310
I was. It was shame.
I've never felt it before.

14:11.393 --> 14:12.686
Makes me want to eat.

14:12.770 --> 14:13.896
Do you have
a craft services table?

14:14.021 --> 14:15.147
No.

14:15.272 --> 14:17.024
Look, if you could
act like that,

14:17.107 --> 14:19.109
without all the pausing
and pretentiousness,

14:19.193 --> 14:21.862
you could be great.

14:21.945 --> 14:26.408
No, Leela. In the world of theater
there are no second acts.

14:28.577 --> 14:31.789
You're not leaving. We're
gonna get you your job baok.

14:31.872 --> 14:33.582
Yeah! How?

14:33.665 --> 14:36.210
He'll <i>audition for</i> a <i>bit part
on All My Circuits</i>

14:36.293 --> 14:37.753
in disguise.

14:37.836 --> 14:41.882
Buthe1lneedto act like we
just saw, modest and sincere.

14:41.965 --> 14:43.801
You really think it'll work?

14:43.884 --> 14:46.053
It sounds like
something that might work.

14:46.136 --> 14:49.264
Vveafing a costume and
pretending to be someone else

14:49.348 --> 14:51.892
goes against my every
instinct as an actor.

14:51.975 --> 14:53.977
But I'll give it a try!

15:02.820 --> 15:05.364
Okay, the audition's
all set up.

15:05.447 --> 15:06.740
Where's Calculon?

15:06.824 --> 15:08.283
And who's this goomer?

15:08.367 --> 15:09.785
(WHISPERING)
It's me, Calculon.

15:09.868 --> 15:10.869
(GASPS)

15:10.953 --> 15:12.287
Okay, just sit tight

15:12.371 --> 15:15.249
till they call the fake name
I made up for you.

15:15.332 --> 15:17.960
Mr. Derisgreat?
Mr. Ben Derisgreat?

15:18.043 --> 15:19.837
(WHISPERING) That's you.
Knock 'em dead.

15:22.589 --> 15:24.341
This is a very minor role.

15:24.425 --> 15:27.803
You'll be playing Calculon, back
from his kidnapping ordeal.

15:27.886 --> 15:28.887
Calculon?

15:28.971 --> 15:32.391
Yes. So make sure your acting
is over the top and horrible.

15:32.474 --> 15:34.560
You literally cannot
do this too crappily.

15:34.643 --> 15:36.311
You've already got the look.

15:36.395 --> 15:39.815
Old, past your prime,
a relic from a lamer era.

15:39.898 --> 15:42.860
You really do look disgusting.
A real Calculon type.

15:42.943 --> 15:44.278
Just... Ugh!

15:44.361 --> 15:45.696
Okay, you know what?
Just hire him.

15:45.821 --> 15:47.114
Done.

15:47.364 --> 15:48.449
(GASPS)

15:51.160 --> 15:54.121
It's humbling to be back on my
old soundstage as a bit player.

15:54.204 --> 15:55.247
Humble is good.

15:55.330 --> 15:56.707
Your self-esteem
took a beating,

15:56.790 --> 15:58.834
but that's what brought
out your true talent.

15:58.917 --> 16:02.296
Yes. You land hard when you
fall from the top, right?

16:02.379 --> 16:06.467
I used to be king here. Now I'm
nothing but a mere peasant.

16:06.550 --> 16:08.635
Or at best, a viscount.

16:08.719 --> 16:10.387
I think "peasant"
is about right.

16:10.471 --> 16:12.931
Duke. On this set,
I'm at least a duke.

16:13.015 --> 16:14.892
My extensive
acting resume dwarfs

16:14.975 --> 16:16.518
that of the average
bit player.

16:16.602 --> 16:18.979
Yes, that's true.
But remember,

16:19.104 --> 16:21.482
it's that kind of
acting that ruined you.

16:21.565 --> 16:24.651
Or maybe archduke. Whichever
one gets to fire the director.

16:24.735 --> 16:26.528
Oh, Lord, here we go.

16:26.612 --> 16:28.906
Look, please just
show some humility,

16:28.989 --> 16:31.492
like the other day when
everything seemed hopeless.

16:31.575 --> 16:35.329
Better yet, I'll whip their
emotions into a frenzy

16:35.412 --> 16:38.165
by taking a dramatic...

16:39.750 --> 16:41.752
Actors to the set!

16:43.086 --> 16:44.546
Okay, here's the scene.

16:44.630 --> 16:46.423
Calculon learns his
wife is unfaithful,

16:46.548 --> 16:48.342
whines about how
pathetic he is,

16:48.425 --> 16:51.762
kills himself, laugh, laugh,
laugh, go to commercial. Got it?

16:51.845 --> 16:53.055
And action!

16:53.138 --> 16:54.848
-~Dause!

16:55.974 --> 16:57.518
Still rolling.

16:57.601 --> 17:00.437
Oh, Calculon, lwish
you had never escaped

17:00.521 --> 17:02.356
from those
brutal crab fishermen.

17:02.439 --> 17:07.402
I want you to know I didn't wait
for you, not even for one day.

17:07.611 --> 17:12.782
(SIGHS) Then I suppose the honorable
thing would be to kill myself,

17:12.866 --> 17:15.536
if I weren't
the legendary Calculon,

17:15.661 --> 17:18.372
the greatest
acting unit of all time!

17:18.454 --> 17:21.875
This show is about me!
And it always has been!

17:21.959 --> 17:24.711
Now, find the co-executive
hack who wrote this drivel

17:24.795 --> 17:29.049
and tell him I want 37 more
climactic speeches by lunch!

17:29.132 --> 17:31.802
Cut! That was terrible!

17:31.885 --> 17:33.053
Just stick to the script.

17:33.136 --> 17:35.389
And if you don't get it on the
second take, you're fired.

17:35.472 --> 17:36.682
Let's take five, people.

17:36.807 --> 17:37.975
(BELL RINGS)

17:38.141 --> 17:39.560
Second take?

17:39.643 --> 17:41.645
I've never heard that phrase,
what does that mean?

17:41.728 --> 17:43.272
They want you
to do it again.

17:43.355 --> 17:44.398
What?

17:44.481 --> 17:46.066
You'll do great.
Just remember,

17:46.149 --> 17:48.485
you're getting devastating
news, so act more humble.

17:48.569 --> 17:50.946
Don't tell me
how to do humble!

17:51.029 --> 17:53.240
My humble ranks
among the greatest

17:53.365 --> 17:55.576
in the history
of the universe!

17:55.659 --> 17:58.370
Now, stand back
and watch the master at work.

17:58.495 --> 17:59.621
Whoo!

17:59.746 --> 18:00.872
You can do it, Calc-y!

18:00.956 --> 18:02.624
No. He can't.

18:02.708 --> 18:03.792
You beg my pardon?

18:03.875 --> 18:05.210
I'm sorry, Calculon,

18:05.294 --> 18:07.421
but someone needs
to remind you of the truth.

18:07.504 --> 18:11.925
You're a grade-B actor who died
and was immediately forgotten.

18:12.009 --> 18:13.927
Leela! That's not very nice.

18:14.011 --> 18:15.929
You're nothing but
a pompous windbag

18:16.013 --> 18:18.765
who lost touch with genuine
emotion years ago.

18:18.849 --> 18:21.602
The sad fact is, we should
have left you dead,

18:21.685 --> 18:24.855
because you can't possibly
do a scene like this.

18:33.697 --> 18:35.949
That was the meanest
thing I ever saw.

18:36.033 --> 18:38.493
Good. Maybe it'll work.

18:38.827 --> 18:40.537
Oh!

18:41.038 --> 18:42.122
(BLARING)

18:42.205 --> 18:43.290
Action!

18:43.373 --> 18:46.251
Oh, Calculon, lwish
you had never escaped

18:46.335 --> 18:48.128
from those
brutal crab fishermen.

18:48.211 --> 18:53.300
I want you to know I didn't wait
for you, not even for one day.

18:53.800 --> 18:58.722
(SIGHS) Then I suppose the honorable
thing would be to kill myself.

19:00.390 --> 19:03.727
I thought I could just
step back into my old life.

19:03.810 --> 19:07.314
But it seems the world
got on fine without me.

19:07.397 --> 19:09.191
Maybe even
a little bit better.

19:09.608 --> 19:10.734
(WHIMPERING)

19:11.068 --> 19:12.402
(BEEPING)

19:12.944 --> 19:15.572
The name Calculon
used to mean something.

19:15.656 --> 19:17.908
Now it's a stain that
will never wash clean.

19:19.910 --> 19:21.244
Farewell.

19:23.538 --> 19:24.873
Cut.

19:25.207 --> 19:26.833
That was incredible.

19:26.917 --> 19:29.211
<i>Who is this
amazing unknown actor?</i>

19:29.294 --> 19:30.587
It is I.

19:31.672 --> 19:32.756
<i>Calculon?</i>

19:32.923 --> 19:34.091
(ALL GASP)

19:40.138 --> 19:42.599
I was programmed to
take credit for this.

19:42.683 --> 19:45.352
Take a bow, Calculon!
You're the greatest!

19:45.435 --> 19:47.979
No. No more bows.

19:48.063 --> 19:50.565
Oh, go ahead,
you've earned it.

19:50.649 --> 19:53.777
Very well. Just one.

19:56.780 --> 19:58.615
Phew! That was close.

20:05.497 --> 20:07.416
And so, on the basis

20:07.499 --> 20:10.836
of one great performance
that almost no one saw,

20:10.919 --> 20:14.506
I'm proud to dedicate
Calculon's posthumous star

20:14.631 --> 20:16.425
on the Walk of Fame!

20:18.760 --> 20:19.845
(ALL CHEERING)

20:22.806 --> 20:25.142
Seems like old times,
huh, Bender?

20:25.225 --> 20:28.311
You and me together,
being fans of Calculon,

20:28.395 --> 20:29.730
not having to talk.

20:29.813 --> 20:31.732
Shut up!
I'm watching the thing!

20:31.815 --> 20:33.400
So am I, buddy,

20:33.483 --> 20:35.277
so am l.

20:41.825 --> 20:43.994
Now, that's more like it.

20:44.077 --> 20:46.955
Always leave them wanting more.
That's the secret.

20:47.122 --> 20:48.373
Ah!

20:48.498 --> 20:49.791
So, what do you say, RD?

20:49.875 --> 20:52.043
Shall I dazzle
the damned with a command

20:52.169 --> 20:54.337
performance of
my one-man show?

20:54.421 --> 20:56.006
Oh, God!

20:56.089 --> 20:59.217
Haven't they suffered enough?

20:59.342 --> 21:00.510
(ROBOTS SCREAMING)
